Some of my favorite #procreate digital paintings created on the iPad :) Please remember that all digital programs are just tools. I went to school for both traditional and digital painting and have been drawing everyday for most of my life. Skills can transfer over from one medium to another. A new program isn’t going to make your art automatically “better” and there is no “secret brush”. Start by just drawing some stuff that you like, draw again, and then do some more drawing! ✍️
.
.
.

🍾🎊Happy New Year! 🎉🥳 I’ve made a promise to myself to share a bit more of #bts in 2023. Back in 2019 I had the pleasure of working with @ditavonteese on this #nye poster! I had a classic illustration approach and started with sketches,thumbnails and color studies. Dita is an icon and I wanted to have more of a painterly approach when it came to the final render. Back then, I spent way too much time over rendering, but it’s great to reflect and see how much has changed from year to year. From this project I learned about the importance of putting a lot of energy into the initial sketches. I also learned how to work in order of importance, big to small. The details can wait :)
.
.
.
#2023 #illustration #art #artoninstagram #draw #sketch #tutorial #digital #painting #conradjavier #tbt #burlesque

🎉First study of #2023 🎉 I’m making it a priority to get more comfortable with @procreate and my iPad. I’m still figuring my workflow, but I’m closing in on my core brushes and approach. Painters out there, do you like direct painting or do you prefer black and white to color process? 

Reference taken from Pinterest - @jewelryedit 
.
.
.
#study #portrait #artist #digitalart #procreate #sketchbook #illustrator #painting #illustration #portraitpainting #conradjavier #wip #daily

This study was admittedly a lot harder than it should’ve been. It’s been so long since I’ve painted on the iPad and I really struggled to find any brush that I felt comfortable with. Maybe it’s a me thing and you never want to blame the “brush”, but this was one of those instances where switching from Photoshop to Procreate wasn’t an easy transition. I think that everyone feels this way when they start to use a new program so I’ll chalk this up to growing pains 😂 That being said, the more that I paint on the iPad, the more I want to use it for commercial work. I’d love to hear from artists out there who use @procreate as their main program for professional work. Please share your favorite #procreate artist in the comments!
.
.
.
#portrait #artist #newyear #drawing #paint #process #wip #reels #sketch #freelance #illustration #draw #conradjavier #digitalart

6 years ago I painted @chancetherapper and my entire life changed. Today marks 6 years of being a self employed illustrator. I had just recently left my 9-5 to pursue a career as a freelancer. It’s amazing to think that one client, one artist, and one day can change the trajectory of your entire life. It’s hard not to get emotional thinking about it because from the moment that I could put pen to paper, I’ve wanted to live a creative life. I know that I say this a lot, but thank you all for your support and positivity. Thank you @bleacherreport and @jordanlchalmers for taking a CHANCE on a new artist. Thank you to #chancetherapper for spreading love through your music. I hope that one day I can thank you in person for changing my life in more ways than one. Thank you family and friends for always pushing me to chase this dream. I’m a little older and wiser, but to be honest not much has changed. I’m still just as hungry and having a damn good time painting my life away. 🙏
.
.
.

I’ve been painting 1 hour key frames before bed from my favorite movies/tv shows and I wanted to share a bit of my process! This study features @thelastofus as I’ve been having withdrawals since the show ended a few weeks ago 😭 I’m really trying to stay loose and experiment as much as I can with different brushes and colors. It’s very similar to how I would approach a traditional painting. It’s best to work big to small and to not focus on making it “look like a photo”. These 1 hour cool downs help me get some much needed practice because it can be hard to experiment when life gets too busy. I tried out the mixer brush in photoshop and it feels like magic. Swipe to see my full process and enjoy! 
.
.
.
#study #practice #draw #sketch #sketchbook #photoshop #painting #digitalpainting #art #artist #movie #hbo #tlou #ellie #videogames #naughtydog #conradjavier

Hey all! Here's another @thelastofus painting study # I really loved the colors in this scene so l gave it a shot! It's quite a bit looser than I usually paint, but just as effective in a study environment. I really tried my best to remember to "KISS" (Keep It Simple Stupid) ) It can be too easy to over render specific sections of the painting when you see a lot of detail. Sometimes you just need to let the brush do a lot of the work and refine later on when vou establish a good base. Swipe for details!
.
